 🔍 Root Cause Analysis

  The issue appears to be at the ECS cluster/infrastructure level:
  - Cluster may not exist or be misconfigured
  - Network configuration preventing Fargate task launch
  - Possible AWS account/region limitations

  🎯 Next Steps for Resolution

  1. Manual AWS Console Investigation
    - Check ECS cluster exists in us-east-1
    - Verify Fargate is enabled
    - Check task stopped reasons in console
  2. Alternative Deployment Options
    - Try EC2 launch type instead of Fargate
    - Deploy to a different AWS region
    - Use ECS CLI for better error visibility
  3. Infrastructure Rebuild
    - Consider recreating the ECS cluster
    - Verify all VPC/subnet configurations
    - Check AWS service quotas

  The distributed TSS application is ready with proper database and Redis connections configured, but requires a functioning ECS environment to run.